        "title": "fix(commandcode): stop repeated 'session depleted' notification after flaky subscription fetch",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- distinguish optional subscription lookup failure from a valid free-tier response\n- preserve Command Code session and quota-warning baselines only during transient enrichment loss\n- keep a freshly depleted paid quota visible when the credits endpoint succeeds but subscription enrichment fails\n- avoid fabricating depletion for startup/free-tier accounts, and clear state again after a valid free-tier response\n- add contributor changelog credit\n\n## Proof\n\n- `swift test --filter CommandCodeQuotaTransitionTests` (3 passed)\n- `swift test --filter CommandCodeUsageFetcherTests` (18 passed)\n- `make check`\n- whole-branch autoreview clean (0.82)\n\nExact reviewed head: `db1b28f3c5d2fd433baf6b2b14410d548a3cbfbf`.\n\nFixes #1624.\n",
